replies.comment info:
@Raquel Pasillas 
When first looking at the graph, I was a little bewildered as to why so much fish and seafood would be wasted, but after reading your comment, it makes a lot more sense. There are a lot more fish than there are cows on this planet, so of course fishers are going to catch several fish compared to a farmer killing one cow. Also, like you said, we can only eat a small part of the fish, unlike meat, where there's a use for every part including organs.  

I think that people are already becoming a lot more aware of what they put into their bodies. There are hundreds of millions of vegetarians in the world, so it’s not like the whole global population is ignorant. I do hope that many others learn as well because with the world entering global extinction, we’ll need a lot more than a couple million.
